# Python Style Guide  

* Use `typing` everywhere (return types, generics).  
* Import order: stdlib › third-party › first-party (enforced by *ruff*).  
* Prefer f-strings; never use `%` formatting.  
* Public functions/methods must have one-line docstrings.  
* Raise explicit exceptions (`ValueError`, `TypeError`) not bare `Exception`.  
* Write pure functions unless interacting with I/O or the network.  
